# JD Resume Builder

AI-driven resume generator that tailors your resume to a specific job description (JD). Parses JD keywords, matches them against your experience, generates STAR-formatted bullets, and exports a single-page A4 PDF.

## Features

- **JD Parsing**: Extracts skills, requirements, and responsibilities from JD text
- **Keyword Matching**: Synonym expansion + priority scoring for accurate alignment
- **STAR Format**: Every bullet follows Situation → Task → Action → Result
- **Bold Highlights**: Key technologies and quantified achievements emphasized
- **Robust 1-Page Control**: 15-level auto-shrink strategy (typography → content → extreme)
  - Phase 1: Shrink font-size (10.5pt → 8.5pt), line-height, margins
  - Phase 2: Prune low-priority content (self-eval → experience → project bullets)
  - Phase 3: Extreme micro-shrink
- **PDF via Edge Headless**: No external dependencies, uses system Edge browser
- **Cache-Resistant**: Time-stamped URLs + disabled browser cache
- **File-Lock Safe**: Time-stamped filenames prevent overwrite conflicts

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/jd-resume-builder.git
cd jd-resume-builder
pip install -e .
```

Requires:
- Python 3.9+
- Microsoft Edge (Windows) or Chromium (Linux/Mac)

## Quick Start

```bash
# Prepare your resume as JSON (see examples/sample_resume.json)
# Prepare JD as plain text (see examples/sample_jd.txt)

jd-resume-builder \
  --resume examples/sample_resume.json \
  --jd examples/sample_jd.txt \
  --output ./output
```

## Resume JSON Format

```json
{
  "name": "Your Name",
  "phone": "13800000000",
  "email": "you@example.com",
  "school": "Your University",
  "major": "Computer Science",
  "degree": "本科",
  "graduation": "2026年6月",
  "location": "苏州",
  "skills": {
    "languages": ["C/C++", "Java", "Python"],
    "frontend": ["Vue3", "HTML/CSS"],
    "backend": ["Spring Boot", "Flask"],
    "database": ["MySQL"],
    "tools": ["Git", "Docker", "Linux"],
    "ai_algo": ["YOLOv11s"]
  },
  "projects": [
    {
      "name": "Project Name",
      "type": "毕业设计",
      "stack": "Vue3 + Spring Boot + MySQL",
      "bullets": ["original bullet 1", "original bullet 2"]
    }
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Company Name",
      "position": "Intern",
      "period": "2023.10 - 2024.04",
      "bullets": ["what you did"]
    }
  ],
  "self_eval": ["your strengths"],
  "honors": ["蓝桥杯省二等奖"],
  "en_levels": [{"name": "CET-4", "score": 530}]
}
```

## CLI Options

```
jd-resume-builder --help

  --resume PATH       Path to resume JSON file (required)
  --jd PATH           Path to JD text file (required)
  --output, -o DIR    Output directory (default: ./output)
  --config, -c PATH   Config YAML file
  --max-pages N       Max pages (default: 1)
  --max-attempts N    Max shrink attempts (default: 15)
  --html-only         Generate HTML only, skip PDF
  --verbose, -v       Verbose logging
```

## Page Control Strategy

When content exceeds `--max-pages`, the controller automatically degrades:

| Phase | Strategy | Details |
|-------|----------|---------|
| 1 | Typography | font-size 10.5pt→10.0→9.5→9.0→8.5, line-height 1.65→1.45 |
| 2 | Content Prune | self-eval last → self-eval all → exp last → exp all → proj2 last → proj2 all → proj1 last |
| 3 | Extreme | font-size continues down to 7.5pt |

Each attempt generates a new PDF and checks page count. Full history is logged.

## Architecture

```
resume_builder/
  cli.py            # argparse entry point
  config.py         # YAML/env configuration
  logger.py         # structured logging
  models.py         # dataclasses (JDProfile, MatchReport, PageControlResult)
  jd_parser.py      # JD text → structured data
  matcher.py        # keyword matching with synonyms
  generator.py      # STAR bullet generation
  renderer.py       # Jinja2 HTML template with dynamic styles
  page_controller.py # robust 1-page controller (15-phase shrink)
  pdf_builder.py    # Edge headless PDF generation
  synonyms.py       # skill synonym dictionary
```

